        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 12 at 2:47PM MDT by NWS Grand Junction CO</headline>
        <description>At 247 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Rifle, or 21 miles west of Glenwood Springs, moving northeast at 30
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Rifle, New Castle, and Silt.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
